replies.bodyText:
It's mostly for good practice (when you get a buffer, you better make sure you either free it or pass it along to someone that will free it). I don't think any lines here are very likely to throw exceptions. However, it is possible. I think the most likely is this one:
         aggregatorSizes[i] = query.getAggregatorSpecs().get(i).getMaxIntermediateSizeWithNulls();
An aggregator could potentially throw an exception from that method for some reason (maybe illegal state, or something). It isn't in the control of the query engine. However, I don't have any examples of where this can actually happen.
